							<hr width="100%" size="1" class="hrcolor" />
							<div class="post">All I know about PID is that it takes a lot of fine tuning to get the correct P,I,D gain values <br />for a particular situation. John is right. I would start with P, and then add in D only. Lastly, do<br />I after the others are set well. Break the problem into parts.<br /><br />For tuning D, you might try just giving the top of the frame a quick push, ie, a sort of <br />impulse function, and playing with the D gain value until it responds properly. Also, you need <br />to be sure you have the &quot;sign&quot; of the gains correct. You want negative feedback, and not<br />positive feedback.<br /><br /></div>
